Description:
BLUE RIBBON LAND SITTING IN THE HEART OF CORINELLA
Showcasing an excellent opportunity to purchase a dream parcel of vacant land in this highly sought after pocket of Corinella. Call Tamara or Daniel today.

Description:
Waterfront 2 Storey Luxury Living
This amazing property offers you beautiful living with stunning sunsets and water views from the living room windows and extensive front deck.
The home has been lovingly renovated in preparation to one day retire to. However circumstances have changed and the owners are now selling the property. Allowing the next owner to fulfill their dream to either enjoy the property as a holiday home, to retire to, a sea change or live in comfort on a permanent basis.
The home features include a new modern kitchen with appliances, a spacious kitchen meals area. Three bedrooms, 2 living rooms, walk in robe and a study. The two fully renovated bathrooms have new floor to ceiling wall tiles, vanities, showers and toilet suites. Polished hardwood floors are a feature in the kitchen / meals area and living room and the home has been freshly painted throughout. New split system plus a wood fire for those cozy winter nights. Under roof line spacious single garage with electric roller door and indoor excess.
Take an early morning or evening stroll to the beach and enjoy those relaxing leisurely walks, simply fish from the sand or relax on the deck with a view to French Island and enjoy a tranquil existence.

Description:
Quiet Area On A Quarter Acre Block
Three bedroom brick veneer home, fully serviced on approximately 1082m2 block.
Master bedroom includes walk in robe and ensuite. A spacious lounge featuring timber raised and raked ceiling fitted with a reverse cycle split system and ceiling fan.
Kitchen has two built in pantries, a wall oven, natural gas stove, dishwasher and lots of cupboard space.
Two living room areas, another reverse cycle split system a natural gas log fire. Good sized Second and third bedrooms, both with built in wardrobes. Outdoor under cover concreted pergola area for that family barbeque. Block has been agi piped for good drainage.
Excellent access to a large backyard through the double gates, a dual carport and double garage under roof line with roller door and concrete floor. Plenty of room to park the caravan, truck or boat. Property has had both side fences replaced. Sun blinds fitted for more add comfort on those hot days.

Address: 15 Island View Rd The Gurdies VIC 3984
Description:
COASTAL LIVING WITH CAPTIVATING BAY VIEWS!!!!
If the time has come to make that sea change but you haven’t quite found the ONE, in an affordable price range, that has bay views and still within commuting distance to CBD, YOU MUST INSPECT THIS PROPERTY!
Positioned in a quiet cul-de-sac, a beautiful peaceful setting, and only minutes to local shops, cafes, the local beach and wineries. This very well kept, split level brick home delivers spacious natural light filled living/meals and kitchen area with dishwasher and large custom designed pantry, looking out to French Island and gorgeous bay views. It has 3 bedrooms, master of generous size with walk in robe and ensuite, tiled floor area for easy maintenance, except all bedrooms have carpet, ceiling fans, split system air conditioner, sliding door to large entertaining deck, plenty of cupboards, family bathroom with full bath and good size laundry. The home has a tranquil feel as soon as you step through the front door. Set on an approximately 770m2 undulating block with double carport and workshop/storage area under house. Just sit back, relax and enjoy the beautiful sunsets, water views and abundant birdlife that this property has to offer - it's just like being on holidays. Close to dual lane highway for easy commute, The Gurdies State Forrest is nearby and major shopping centres and Phillip Island are approximately 25 minutes away.

COASTAL INVESTMENT PERMIT FOR 7 LOT SUBDIVISION

Description:
BEACHSIDE LIVING
This property has it all. On offer is a renovated 3 bedroom home on a substantial corner block of approx. 1,170 sq.m. Featuring open plan living and meals area with timber floors, sliding door to deck, 7 kw. Split-system air conditioner, modern kitchen with stainless steel appliances, island bench and plenty of cupboards. Wide entrance with door to separate deck area, wood heater, ceiling fan, modern family bathroom and good size laundry with bench space and storage. The property offers different zones for kids play area or pets, garden/wood shed, chook pen and veggie garden plus a 3 bay size shed with 2 roller doors and separate entrance ideal for boat, caravan or truck. The house area also has separate driveway with gates and parking area.
Potential for subdivision STCA. Tenby Point is a no through road to water’s edge with rural outlook and native settings. Only minutes to a 24-hour boat ramp, local shop, school bus, v-line service, and approx. 7 minutes to shops with permanent doctor, Chemist, bank, cafes and ambulance depot. Easy commute to CBD with dual lane highway and major shopping centre and Phillip Island approx. 25 mins. This is an ideal investment property or a great family residence with plenty of space.

FANTASTIC BLOCK 150 METERS FROM FORESHORE
On offer is a rare opportunity to secure a block in an amazing location in the hub of Grantville.
Build a two storey ( STCA ) and look forward to uninterrupted sunsets and summer days enjoyed at the beach with this fantastically positioned 369sqm approx. allotment that is ready & waiting for you to build the home or holiday house you have always wanted in a location many desire.

This thriving community offers a great life style including great tourist events, Penguin parade, local vine yards and much more and is only 40 Minutes to the world-famous GP track.
